# md2pdf: Markdown-to-PDF Generation

When the user asks to build a PDF from markdown, or when you encounter a `report.yaml` file:

## The Tool

`md2pdf` is installed at `~/.local/bin/md2pdf`. It reads `report.yaml` from the
project root and combines ordered markdown sections into a styled PDF via WeasyPrint.

## Commands

```bash
md2pdf                      # build from ./report.yaml
md2pdf path/to/report.yaml  # explicit config
md2pdf --init               # scaffold a report.yaml in cwd
```

## Config Format (report.yaml)

```yaml
title: My Report
footer: "Footer text for each page"
output: report/output.pdf
sections:
  - report/01-intro.md
  - report/02-body.md
css: optional/override.css      # optional, replaces default styles
combined: report/_combined.md   # optional, writes merged markdown
```

## Pipeline

1. Combines markdown sections in listed order (separated by `---`)
2. Converts to HTML via python-markdown (tables, extra, sane_lists)
3. Resolves relative image paths to file:// URIs
4. Applies CSS (embedded default or project override)
5. Renders to PDF via WeasyPrint

## Dependencies

- `weasyprint` (Homebrew): `brew install weasyprint`
- `markdown` (pip): `pip3 install markdown`

## When Setting Up a New Project

1. Run `md2pdf --init` to scaffold report.yaml
2. Edit sections list to match the project's markdown files
3. Run `md2pdf` to build
